                <h1>Newly elected Academic Council Chair Kerry Haynie looks ahead at two-year term</h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/4ec6c004-1c81-4369-906c-7aca073b7267.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="Special&#x20;to&#x20;the&#x20;Chronicle" class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            Special to the Chronicle

                            
                        </div>
                    </figure>
                
                                    <div class="row  mt-4 mb-0 mb-md-4">
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                            <aside class="author-name">
                                    
    
                                    
            By <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/maram-elnagheeb">Maram Elnagheeb</a>
                                    
                                <div class="mt-1">
                                    <span class="can-localize">April 23, 2019 | 3:10am EDT</span>
                                </div>
                            </aside>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 text-left text-md-right d-print-none">
                            <ul class="social-links list-unsyled list-inline mt-4 mt-md-0">
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2019/04/kerry-haynie-duke-university-academic-council-chair-elected-financial-aid" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-facebook"></i></a></li>
